    {
      "id": "0922f1e6-8598-4340-99a2-5407b9c611fa",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Most educators and managers often rely on domain knowledge and intuition to predict students at risk. The paper reviews current methods used in LA and concludse that few approaches actually delve into early prediction. Authors subsequently re-define student attendance AND create a model that, by Week 3 of the Fall Semester achieved an Accuracy of 97%. No specific additional details are provided in the current moment.",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
